  <text>
    <body>
      <ab type="lido:objectWorkType">Leaflet</ab>
      <ab subtype="creation" type="lido:event">
        <date>1943 after</date>
      </ab>
      <ab type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">The frameless leaflet features a collage of two photographs. The image on the bottom left depicts a couple embracing each other on a skiff. The man is wearing a dark uniform and a dark peaked cap, the woman is in a long light-coloured dress with dark double stripes. The dominant image on the top right shows a young woman in a light-coloured dress with a black bow. She is wearing a striking hat with a birdcage veil. The Serbo-Croatian title ‘Jesenja melodija’ (Autumn melody) is indicated in a red field overlapping the two pictures. The German original film title was ‘Liebesgeschichten’ (Love stories).</ab>
      <ab subtype="comment" type="lido:objectDescriptionSet">Willy Fritsch and Hannelore Schroth were cast as the couple, Herta Mayen as the young woman. The film was directed by Viktor Tourjansky and released in 1943.</ab>
